Majority Leader of the House of Representatives, Alhaji Alhassan Ado Doguwa, has said his political future lies with Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje. Speaking when he led a large number of people from Rano Emirate to thank Governor Ganduje for supporting his candidature as majority leader, Doguwa said he never regretted associating with Ganduje. “Governor Ganduje has done everything to me in my journey to become majority leader,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “He stood by me throughout the struggle. The governor is the kind of leader that whoever associates with him will never regret his action,” he said. Responding, Governor Ganduje assured that he would continue to support Doguwa in his political undertakings. “I would have supported him to become speaker of the house if the arrangement warrants that,” he said.  90% of people kidnapped in Kano rescued  - Ganduje Kwankwaso, Ganduje factions disagree on peace terms 2019: Can Kano APC survive Gandujiyya, Kwankwasiyya rivalry? Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin